President Trump visited H&K Equipment in Pennsylvania to promote the benefits of the recently passed tax cuts. He praised the workers and the company for their success and announced that H&K Equipment will be making a $2.7 million capital investment thanks to the new tax cuts. Trump also highlighted the positive effects of the tax cuts, such as increased wages, lower energy bills, and job creation. He mentioned that millions of workers have already received tax-cut bonuses from their employers, and companies like Apple and Comcast have announced bonuses for their employees as well. Trump emphasized the importance of American workers and the American Dream, and vowed to continue working to make America great again.